From: Christopher L. Crutchfield <ccrutchf@ucsd.edu>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 19:30:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] phy: samsung-gs101-ufs: fix two PMA register transcription
 typos in tensor_gs101_pre_init_cfg

The pre-init PMA configuration table for the Tensor SoCs has two
entries that target registers AOSP's cal-if never writes, while
omitting two entries that AOSP unconditionally does write. Both
look like single-digit transcription mistakes between the AOSP byte
offset (`0x9F4` / `0xAF8`) and the mainline register-index
representation used by `PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101` (= byte / 4).

  AOSP gs201 ufs-cal-if `init_cfg_evt0`:
    {0x0000, 0x9F4, 0x01, ..., PHY_PMA_TRSV, ...}
    {0x0000, 0xAF8, 0x06, ..., PHY_PMA_TRSV, ...}

  Current mainline `tensor_gs101_pre_init_cfg`:
    PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x25D, 0x01, ...)   /* byte 0x974 */
    PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x29E, 0x06, ...)   /* byte 0xA78 */

`0x974` differs from `0x9F4` by one swapped hex digit, and `0xA78`
from `0xAF8` likewise. Neither `0x974` nor `0xA78` is written by
AOSP's gs101, gs201 or zuma cal-if. The mainline writes therefore:

  - Touch registers AOSP never touches (whose default value is
    presumably the intended state).
  - Skip the two writes AOSP does perform.

The bogus `0x25D=0x01` write also clobbers an earlier
`0x25D=0x00` entry at the top of the same table, so the final
register value also disagrees with AOSP for byte `0x974`.

Fix both entries to point at the registers AOSP actually writes
(`0x27D` and `0x2BE`). Tested on Pixel Fold (felix, gs201): the
fix is observable in PHY calibration state (`TRSV_REG338` /
`LN0_MON_RX_CAL_DONE` register reads at the entry to
`gs101_phy_wait_for_cdr_lock` differ run-to-run after the change),
but it is not on its own sufficient to make HS-Rate-B CDR lock work
on gs201. The fix is nonetheless correct vs the AOSP reference
driver and worth landing on its own. (The remaining HS-Rate-B
issue on gs201 is the subject of a separate investigation.)

The table is currently shared by `gs101_ufs_phy_drvdata` and
`tensor_gs201_ufs_phy_drvdata`. AOSP's gs101 cal-if does not
write `0x9F4` or `0xAF8`, so this patch adds two extra PMA writes
for gs101 too. Those writes are unconditional defaults in AOSP's
gs201 path with no PMD/board gating, and the gs101 PHY register
file shares the same layout, so the additional writes are
expected to be benign. A cleaner long-term solution is to split
the table per-SoC, but that is out of scope for a typo fix.

Signed-off-by: Christopher L. Crutchfield <ccrutchf@ucsd.edu>
Cc: Peter Griffin <peter.griffin@linaro.org>
Cc: Alim Akhtar <alim.akhtar@samsung.com>
Cc: Vinod Koul <vkoul@kernel.org>
Cc: Kishon Vijay Abraham I <kishon@kernel.org>
Cc: linux-phy@lists.infradead.org
Cc: linux-samsung-soc@vger.kernel.org
Cc: linux-arm-kernel@lists.infradead.org
---
 drivers/phy/samsung/phy-gs101-ufs.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/phy/samsung/phy-gs101-ufs.c b/drivers/phy/samsung/phy-gs101-ufs.c
--- a/drivers/phy/samsung/phy-gs101-ufs.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/samsung/phy-gs101-ufs.c
@@ -60,7 +60,7 @@ static const struct samsung_ufs_phy_cfg tensor_gs101_pre_init_cfg[] = {
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x284, 0x02, PWR_MODE_ANY),
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x285, 0x02, PWR_MODE_ANY),
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x2A2, 0x04, PWR_MODE_ANY),
-	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x25D, 0x01, PWR_MODE_ANY),
+	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x27D, 0x01, PWR_MODE_ANY),
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x2FA, 0x01, PWR_MODE_ANY),
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x286, 0x03, PWR_MODE_ANY),
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x287, 0x03, PWR_MODE_ANY),
@@ -75,7 +75,7 @@ static const struct samsung_ufs_phy_cfg tensor_gs101_pre_init_cfg[] = {
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x2BB, 0x06, PWR_MODE_ANY),
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x2BC, 0x06, PWR_MODE_ANY),
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x2BD, 0x06, PWR_MODE_ANY),
-	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x29E, 0x06, PWR_MODE_ANY),
+	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x2BE, 0x06, PWR_MODE_ANY),
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x2E4, 0x1a, PWR_MODE_ANY),
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x2ED, 0x25, PWR_MODE_ANY),
 	PHY_TRSV_REG_CFG_GS101(0x269, 0x1a, PWR_MODE_ANY),
--
2.43.0
